I b. 39. 4.—Ibi regnator omnium deUS (of the local religion of the Sem- nones). The only passage where Tacitus uses deus in a monotheistic sense 3 in his account of Jewish monotheism (Hist. v. 5. 6), he uses the vaguer word numen, apparently thinking, like Strabo, that such spiritual theism verges on pantheism,-some called it atheism.
